title: Arts Funding
name: Arts Funding
description:
Public arts funding distributed by the San Francisco Arts Commission. Total district funding includes funding allocated for: Civic Design Review, Community Arts and Education, Cultural Equity Grants, Public Art, Civic Art Collection and Monument Conservation, and Street Artists Program. Attributes for each supervisorial district include the total SFAC funding, the population, per capita funding, and the percentage of SFAC funding received. 

Public funding for the arts is being used to assure spaces for libraries, performing arts, theatre, museums, concerts, and festivals for personal and educational fulfillment.

Data from San Francisco Arts Commission, 2009 District Based Annual Report.    

For further information see www.thehdmt.org
